party.description: Geneva Bioinformatics (GeneBio) SA is a leading bioinformatics company providing the life sciences community with world-class software that bridges the gap between information gathering and knowledge generation. Established in 1997, we focus our expertise on Mass Spectrometry characterization of proteins and small molecules as well as proteome imaging, offering clients and partners a high degree of specialization essential to their research. Close ties to academic peers and a thorough network of distribution and strategic partners give us both unfettered access to scientific excellence and recognized market presence so that we may best serve the scientific community.
